  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to evaluate if Electromagnetic navigation (ENB) in combination with
      rapid on site evaluation (ROSE) can improve diagnostic accuracy in those patients who fail to
      be diagnosed with conventional fluoroscopic assisted bronchoscopy (FBS) in combination with
      ROSE.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
